title: BUILDING LOG HOMES
description:
This book. The Handbook of Canadian Log
Building, is designed for use by anyone in the log
building industry: a once-in-a-lifetime builder, or the
professional, hand-crofted log builder using these
skills to earn a living. It is meant to be a reference
book as well for building authorities and teaching
institutions who must make it their business to
become familiar with the latest techniques of the
trade
